    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&amp;rsquo;m James. I build &lt;a href=&#34;https://taco.build&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Threshold Cryptography&lt;/a&gt;  tools and protocols.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I care about privacy, governance, and autonomy: giving people and communities the ability to rely less on centralized authorities and concentrated power.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m trying to get better at building things that directly impact the world, rather than just nice ideas.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here you&amp;rsquo;ll find &lt;a href=&#34;./posts&#34;&gt;essays and tutorials&lt;/a&gt; , and links to &lt;a href=&#34;./talks&#34;&gt;talks&lt;/a&gt;  I&amp;rsquo;ve given.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My bias: I think most people are good, and I&amp;rsquo;m optimistic about the future. I worry about the small percentage of people who crave power. The things they do with that power. And the systems that enable their behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
